HB 481 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Riser
Abstract: Provides for compensation for publication of official proceedings and public
notices.
Present law authorizes parishes, municipalities, and school boards to publish their official
proceedings and public notices by contract. Provides that payment may be made monthly
or quarterly.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law (R.S. 43:147.1) provides for maximum rates based on price per character, unless
parties agree to a higher rate. Provides that "character" does not include spaces, letting, or
kerning. Provides that the maximum rate is two cents per character if the parish has a city
with a population of more than 100,000 and one and one-half cents per character if the parish
does not have a city with a population of more than 100,000.
Proposed law increases the maximum rates based on price per character. Provides that the
maximum rate is three cents per character in all parishes.
