Present law (R.S. 43:147) provides for maximum rates that an official journal may charge
generally as follows:
(1) $6 per square of 100 words in parishes that do not contain a city with a population
greater than 100,000.
(2) $.33 per agate line in parishes that contain a city with a population of greater than
100,000 but no city with a population greater than 300,000.
(3) $.37 per agate line in parishes that contain a city with a population greater than
300,000.
Present law (R.S. 43:147.2) provides that from Jan. 1, 2024, through Dec. 31, 2026, a journal
may submit a bid pursuant to present law (R.S. 43:147) or present law (R.S. 43:147.1) or
both, at the journal's option. Provides that beginning Jan. 1, 2027, a journal shall submit bids
pursuant to present law (R.S. 43:147.1), unless the governing body requests otherwise.
Proposed law retains present law and provides that the cost of publishing official
proceedings and public notices shall not exceed the lesser of the rates provided for in
proposed law or the rate in effect on January 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 43:147.1(B)(1) and(2); Adds R.S. 43:147.1(D))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Add provisions providing that the cost of publishing official proceedings and
public notices shall not exceed the lesser of the rates provided for in proposed
law or the rate in effect on January 1, 2026.
2. Remove provision that requires parishes, municipalities, and school boards to
publish official proceedings and public notices by contract.
3. Make technical changes.
